            . I live with Mr. Higham, a pawnbroker. On the 10th of April, I took a volume of Shakspeare's works in pawn - another young man wrote the ticket; that and another book were together. We advanced 3 s. 6 d. on them I believe the prisoner is the man who pawned them, but will not be positive.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-164-person1427">
                  CORNELIUS 
                  BOWER
               <interp inst="t18240603-164-person1427" type="surname" value="BOWER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-164-person1427" type="given" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-164-person1427" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am beadle of St. Giles's. On the 24th of April I was sent, and apprehended the prisoner in Mr. Wright's shop, and found thirty-two duplicates on him; one of them was for Mr. Wright's books. I found 9 s. 8 d. on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-164-person1428">
                  PETER 
